properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 14 at 2:38AM PST until February 15 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Combined seas 6 to 8 ft building to 13 to 15 feet through
the morning hours. Bar conditions moderate becoming rough to
severe with breakers possible.

* WHERE...Grays Harbor Bar.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Maximum ebb currents will occur around 830
AM and 845 PM Friday.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory for rough bar means that wave conditions
are expected to be hazardous to small craft in or near harbor
entrances.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM PST SATURDAY
